official-title.#text:
To prohibit employers and certain other entities from
		  requiring or requesting that employees and certain other individuals provide a
		  user name, password, or other means for accessing a personal account on any
		  social networking website.

committee-name.#text:
Committee on Education and the
			 Workforce

cosponsor.#tail:
) introduced the
			 following bill; which was referred to the

text.#text: This Act may be cited as the

header.#text:
Employer Access
			 to Personal Accounts on Social Networking Websites

text.#text:
It shall be
			 unlawful for any employer—

to require or
			 request that an employee or applicant for employment provide the employer with
			 a user name, password, or any other means for accessing a private email account
			 of the employee or applicant or the personal account of the employee or
			 applicant on any social networking website; or

to discharge, discipline, discriminate
			 against in any manner, or deny employment or promotion to, or threaten to take
			 any such action against, any employee or applicant for employment
			 because—

the employee or applicant for employment
			 refuses or declines to provide a user name, password, or other means for
			 accessing a private email account of the employee or applicant or the personal
			 account of the employee or applicant on any social networking website;
			 or

such employee or applicant for employment
			 has filed any complaint or instituted or caused to be instituted any proceeding
			 under or related to this Act or has testified or is about to testify in any
			 such proceeding.

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail:
, any employer who violates any provision of this Act may be assessed a
			 civil penalty of not more than $10,000.

			 under this section to restrain violations of this Act. In any action brought

			 jurisdiction, for cause shown, to issue temporary or permanent restraining

header.#text:
Institution of
			 higher education access to personal accounts on social networking

text.#text:
The institution will
				not—

require or request

				password, or any other means for accessing a private email account of the

				potential student on any social networking website; or

discharge, discipline, discriminate against
				in any manner, or deny admission to, suspend, or expel, or threaten to take any

the student or potential student refuses or
				declines to provide a user name, password, or other means for accessing a
				private email account of the student or potential student or the personal
				account of the student or potential student on any social networking website;
				or

such student or potential student has filed
				any complaint or instituted or caused to be instituted any proceeding under or
				related to this paragraph or has testified or is about to testify in any such
				proceeding.

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.@value: Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965/t:IX/pt:E/spt:2

header.#text:
Prohibition on
				access to personal accounts of students

text.#text:
No local educational
				agency receiving funds under this Act may—

require or request
				that a student or potential student provide the agency or a school served by
				the agency with a user name, password, or any other means for accessing a
				private email account of the student or potential student or the personal
				account of the student or potential student on any social networking website;
				or

discharge, discipline, discriminate against
				in any manner, or deny admission to, suspend, or expel, or threaten to take any
				such action against, any student or potential student because—

the student or potential student refuses or
				declines to provide a user name, password, or other means for accessing a
				private email account of the student or potential student or the personal
				account of the student or potential student on any social networking website;
				or

such student or potential student has filed
				any complaint or instituted or caused to be instituted any proceeding under or
				related to this paragraph or has testified or is about to testify in any such
				proceeding.

Sec. 9537. Prohibition on access to
				personal accounts of
				students.

text.#text: As used in this Act—

term.#tail:
means any person acting directly or indirectly in the
			 interest of an employer in relation to an employee or an applicant for
			 employment; and

text.#text: the term

term.#tail:
means any Internet service, platform, or website that provides a
			 user with a distinct account—

text.#text: the term

whereby the user
			 can access such account by way of a distinct user name, password, or other

that is primarily
